		<content type="html" xml:base="http://skysedge.us/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1482&amp;p=1508#p1508"><![CDATA[
Yeah it's a bit wierd the first time, then the setting is remembered and it becomes easy.<br><br>I think you're trying to export the BoM from the PCB Layout Editor. I just tried this for the first time and the CSV export was a mess - I'm not going to try and fault find because another method works well.<br><br>I export BoMs from the Schematic Layout Editor (logical to me since this is where component values are entered). Click the BoM symbol in the schematic editor. Now the fun part but you only need to do this once; click the '+' button to add a BoM template and navigate to:<br>    C:\Program Files\KiCad\bin\scripting\plugins\          (yeah I'm hampered by Windows, sorry)<br>Look for Python scripts and select one (these are the BoM format templates) then click 'Generate'.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://skysedge.us/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1724">SteveC</a> — Sun Apr 19, 2020 12:04 pm</p><hr />
